reviews.text:
Horrible service, we were accused of leaving without paying!

My boyfriend and I went in on Monday 2/11/2019 to celebrate our anniversary. We wanted to try something new so we went to Buca wanting to have a good time.

The service was slow and our server always spoke to us ridiculously fast, we had trouble understanding her most of the time. 

The food portions are quite large and enough for leftovers, I'll give them that.

We finally payed, we left the restaurant and got in the car when we noticed a manager and an employee standing outside the restaurant, when suddenly the employee ran to our car and knocked on the window. He asked if we had taken the checkbook with us. He confused my black wallet for the checkbook and thought we left without paying!!!! He didn't bother checking our table for the checkbook or asking our server if we had paid before leaving, he followed us to our car and asked us. That is no way to handle a situation like that! I had never been treated that way at any place, it was infuriating! I will never return here or recommend this place to anyone.

If you want to try good Italian food and not get harassed in the parking lot by the employees over a wallet, go to Eddies Italian Eatery which is only 2-3 blocks down, the food is amazing and the service is exceptional.

Buyer beware.    What a huge disappointment.   Made a reservation for my boyfriends birthday.  Just the two of us. Was hoping for a special night.   But when we wanted to order we found out that we were required to order and pay for 3 people and 3 portions of anything on the menu.  This doesn’t make sense to me.  We wanted to each try something different but didn’t want or need that much food.  As long as this is the policy we won’t be going back.    
Management should definitely reconsider the minimum 3 person requirement  before they loose more and more customers

I've always loved Italian food, buca is no exception. My first time at this location was tonight, and it was good. It was rainy, so everyone waited in the lobby,  which was crowded, but the atmosphere makes you forget about the discomfort for a little bit. There are so many little details to observe and keep you busy for a bit. Everyone was friendly and warm, it felt so welcoming. The food is something else here. Buca has the best Italian food you can get in America, even though it's a large chain. The shrimp scampi was so buttery and delicious, get that for sure if you like shrimp. Spaghetti and meatballs is a classic choice you can't go wrong with, plus the meatballs are all beef! Love love love

I've only been here twice. But each time the food has been fresh and delicious! The service is great and staff is super friendly. But definitely come hungry and ready to share! I would definitely come back again.

Had a great evening tonight. Dinner was perfectly cooked and our waiter was awesome. His name was Shawn(I really hope that I spelled that right). He was polite, funny, and a great server. My glass was never empty and he kept coming by at the right time. But, he was not over intrusive. Food was great and the service was even better. Thanks again for a great evening.

The turkey flight sandwich was delicious and large. They carve the turkey breast for the sandwich right there, and it was very moist. We could have split one sandwich. The curly fries were perfectly crispy.

Probably deserves a 1-star but I'm not the demographic they're aiming for so I'll give some credit. If you like some unique salads, and don't mind paying a bit more for lunch, this is the place for.  Some unique sandwich choices also. The atmosphere is alright, location nice for a downtown Chico restaurant, and they have some fun and pretty good baked goods always on display under glass for purchase. The most memorable part was the curly fries; very tasty.

The problem with Pluto's is every dish is prepared with so much undesirable ingredients and options, or is lacking what you might expect on food. Sandwiches that should clearly be prepared hot aren't and they RACK UP THE COST on anything if you want to add to it. Just adding some basic veggies and a dressing on a salad costs a few bucks. Any meat substitution or adding is costly as well. I never enjoy my meal and it's always so pricey. Hope you can change for the better Pluto's.
Great portions, fresh produce. Definitely felt prices were reasonable. Service was quick and friendly. They bus tables.
This place was really fun.  The food was delicious and healthy. I love that I was able to build my own salad.

So does okay. Imaginative but the taste Is Not Great. Not bad either. Not for families. It looks a little beat up. And the standing at different stations to order food is confusing and impractical. Especially with children
korean food here - excellent. Do yourself a favor and try this place. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
Deliciousness all around! I have come to this location a couple of times. I've tried the Beef Short Rib Bento box (my favorite), Pork Bento box,  and the Dumpling Sampler.
Great food, convenient location (right next to Korean supermarket), friendly staff and next to no waiting time. One minor point is the plastic spoon to eat with..

Chicken bento box was delicious and fresh. It was ready in about 5 minutes during the lunch hour. Lots of choices between this restaurant stand and the sushi stand next to it. There's a coffee bar and bakery in the lobby too.
This place is inside of H Mart. They have SGD Tofu near loop!  the taste about the same as the one in the burbs. They only give you two side dishes, kimchi and oh deng (fish cake)
